"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/HOTVjRYGdc5P3xXPmoXox.jpg?height=800&width=1280&size=large)\\n\\n## Why SODL?\\n\\nOver the past few years,\\n\\nThe price of BTC was rising from $0.09 in 2010 to $48,000 now;\\n\\nThe price of ETH was rising from $0.31 in 2014 to $3,800 now;\\n\\n......\\n\\nDid you own them once?\\n\\nDo you still have them?\\n\\nIn another words:\\n\\nDid you **HODL** or **SODL** them?\\n\\nCome on! There's nothing embarrassing. We all did dummy things in life.\\n\\nHere you can find what SBF did: [SBF wallet on sodl.xyz](https://app.sodl.xyz/address/0x84d34f4f83a87596cd3fb6887cff8f17bf5a7b83?dex=uniswap_v2&filterBy=ALL)\\n\\nDo you remember **Laszlo Hanyecz**?\\n\\nNO?\\n\\nDo you know what is Bitcoin pizza day and why we celebrate it?\\n\\nIn brief, **Laszlo Hanyecz** bought two pizzas with **10,000 BTC** on May 22, **2010**.\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/7nevPxhxWOE4olMRsldSw.jpeg?height=800&width=800)\\n\\nDid he regret it?\\n\\nHere is what he said:\\n\\n> ‚ÄúI've never seen Bitcoin as an investment, and while it's easy to look back and say ‚ÄòI could have been a millionaire,‚Äô I think it's¬†**more important to look at the mindset**¬†I had during the pizza transaction, not being that of acquiring an investment, but of¬†**making use of a form of currency**. If I was looking to hoard coins, I very likely¬†**wouldn't have been in the right place at the right time**.‚Äù\\n\\nWe celebrate it and remember him, because he is the **daredevil** who used BTC as a kind of currency in real life.\\n\\nWe know this story is real because the transaction on blockchain is real.\\n\\n[https://twitter.com/coinbase/status/1396112764599357448](https://twitter.com/coinbase/status/1396112764599357448)\\n\\nThose who swap tokens only in CEX are just **traders**.\\n\\nWe are the damn real **web3r**!\\n\\n[https://twitter.com/Cooopahtroopa/status/1471572923085246467](https://twitter.com/Cooopahtroopa/status/1471572923085246467)\\n\\n## What is $SODL?\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/8zRSVGnGzF3Z5_2lrzH-E.png?height=1000&width=1000)\\n\\nThe philosophy behind $SODL token was to express ‚Äî‚Äî\\n\\nüôÅ¬†means:\\n\\n* I **SODL**\\n* I got a¬†**rug pull**\\n* The DeFi project got¬†**hacked**\\n\\n‚úåÔ∏èmeans:\\n\\n* It is¬†**okay**\\n* **Forget it**\\n* I can **move on**\\n* I love **decentralization**\\n* I love **cryptocurrency**\\n\\nThe most important part you may care about: **tokenomics**!\\n\\n![$SODL tokenomics](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/dHuw01KV6X9pJW1pRFeC7.png?height=536&width=812)\\n\\nThat‚Äôs quite simple, right?\\n\\n**The team won‚Äôt reserve any token. We get rewarded ONLY if you vote.**\\n\\nThe first rule of **$SODL** mint is ‚Äî‚Äî\\n\\nDo not mint **$SODL** without any proof, which means **$SODL** can only be minted by a proving **SODL** TX. A SODL TX means the token value you used to swap from now is lower than the token value you swapped into.\\n\\nBased on this rule, the team can't mint **$SODL** for themselves.\\n\\n## How $SODL works?\\n\\nIf you used to swap tokens on Uniswap v2, Uniswap V3 or Sushi, you may have chance to claim $SODL. Currently, we support those tokens:\\n\\n 1. ETH/WETH\\n 2. USDT\\n 3. DAI\\n 4. USDC\\n 5. WBTC\\n 6. YFI\\n 7. UNI\\n 8. SAND\\n 9. SHIB\\n10. SUSHI\\n\\nIf you swapped tokens in above list to another, you may be able to claim $SODL with that tx hash,  the amount is how much you save in dollars if you did swap. Please note, that **doesn‚Äôt mean $SODL is $1**, it‚Äôs just easy to **remember how much you SODL**.\\n\\nFor example, if you lose $100 in some tx, you can claim 100 $SODL. Of course, you can come back later, after all, the market is changing always. The money you lose is changing too.\\n\\nAccess <https://app.sodl.xyz> and have a try.\\n\\n## How vote works?\\n\\nAfter claim, you can use $SODL to vote for more tokens to be listed.\\n\\nFor example, you SODL FTM in 2020, and it shows you save $10,000 if you didn‚Äôt swap. You can pay 1,000 $SODL to vote for FTM with that tx hash. You may get about 10,000 $SODL(the amount depends on the prices of tokens) once FTM is listed.\\n\\n### When will a new token be listed?\\n\\nOnce the contribution of $SODL (the amount of all used to be voted) is more than 10% of $SODL total minted, the top token will be listed and the contribution of the top token will be transferred to dev team.\\n\\nFor example, if there are A, B and C token in voting list, and they get contributed 300, 200 and 100 $SODL each other. Let‚Äôs assume that we have minted 6,000 $SODL, the contribution reaches 10%, token A will be listed and 300 $SODL will be transferred to dev team. And now the contribution becomes 5%, then you go to claim $SODL of token A.\\n\\nThe token list system only works when we get enough holders, otherwise it‚Äôs easy to be manipulated.\\n\\nSo **HODL** on.\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/HEpub60jKxEOhz8cBcHDn.gif?height=250&width=331)\\n\\nThe funds of the team will be used for further development and growth of SODL, such as grants, hackathons, meetups and more... If you‚Äôre interested, check our [roadmap](https://www.sodl.xyz/#roadmap).\\n\\n## Conclusion\\n\\n[https://twitter.com/Cooopahtroopa/status/1473365790858506240](https://twitter.com/Cooopahtroopa/status/1473365790858506240)\\n\\nFinally, not a financial advice, don‚Äôt **SODL** again.\\n\\nOfficial Website: <https://www.sodl.xyz/>\\n\\nOfficial Twitter: <https://twitter.com/sodldao>\\n\\nOfficial Discord: <https://discord.gg/28kzMnjreN>\",\"timestamp\":1640878273,\"title\":\"The DAO for $OLDers\"},\"digest\":\"3z95LhPmRm880og2Ci-_riJRGKXPgIwCKQElsbI_M1E\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xc8399CA553E74894c211B55a85AC9E16D8a2751e\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"WQluOR-Q39jzm